<%= simple_form_for @practitioner, :html => { :class => 'form-horizontal' } do |f| %>

<p>
  This is a demonstration of two different styles of selecting an associated model: <b>Modality</b>. If your desired choice is not on the list, you may add it.
</p>
<p>
  In the <em>Old Manual Method</em>, only one choice is permitted. You may choose from the standard list, or choose "Other modality...". A new input field will appear and allow you to enter the new item.
</p>
<p>
  With the <em>New Chosen Method</em>, you may choose as many existing modalities as you like, or type in new ones.
</p>
<hr/>

  <%= f.input :name %>

  <div class="row" style="background-color:lightgray">
    <div class="span5">
      <p><b>Old Manual Method</b></p>
      <%= f.association :modality %>
    </div>

    <div class="span5">
      <p><b>New Chosen Method</b></p>
      <%= f.association :modality %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-actions">
    <%= f.submit nil, :class => 'btn btn-primary' %>
    <%= link_to t('.cancel', :default => t("helpers.links.cancel")),
                practitioners_path, :class => 'btn' %>
  </div>
<% end %>
